Ever grown a classic variety with memorably epic results, only to find out the variety has subsequently been discontinued? ❌⁠
⁠
The good news is that sometimes your favourite discontinued strains have a close genetic match. Dutch Passion have been around since the 1980’s. In that time, some very special varieties have come and gone. If you have ever wanted to see a legendary variety re-emerge like a phoenix, then this blog is just for you! 🔥⁠⁠

node.text:
Leaves contain the natural pigment called chlorophyll. This allows photosynthesis to occur in the leaves, converting light energy into chemical/biological energy for growth. On the under side of leaves are small pores called stomata. During photosynthesis these allow carbon dioxide to enter the cells as well as allowing oxygen and water vapour to escape. 🍀⁠
⁠
Cannabis leaves are remarkable pieces of multi purpose cellular technology, they can also absorb nutrients fed directly to them in a process known as foliar feeding. 🍽️⁠
⁠
📸 On this beautiful picture taken by @percy.crops you see some leaves from our Bubba Island Kush ⁠
🔗 Link in our bio⁠
⁠
#green #leaf #chlorophyll #photosynthesis ⁠#happysaturday #goodvibes ⁠
